The paper presents a fully dynamic algorithm for maintaining all pairs all shortest paths in a directed graph with positive real weights on each edge. This problem is related to various areas of computer science, including data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational geometry (cs.CG), network analysis (cs.NI), and social and information networks (cs.SI). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CG, cs.NI, and cs.SI, in that order.
